article.headline: Harvard 27, Princeton 10
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Chris Pizzotti passed for a career high 365 yards and two touchdowns to lead Harvard to a 27-10 win over Princeton in the 100th meeting between the teams on Saturday. Harvard (4-2, 3-0 Ivy) scored on its first two possessions -- a 41-yard touchdown reception by Corey Mazza and a 23-yard field goal by Patrick Long. But the Tigers (2-4, 1-2) tied it on Connor Louden's 34-yard field goal early in the second quarter and a 29-yard touchdown run by R.C. Lagomarsino. Long's 28-yard field goal with just over a minute to play in the first half gave the Crimson a 13-10 halftime lead. Cheng Ho, who rushed for 113 yards, scored on a 1-yard run on Harvard's first possession of the second half. Ho also had three catches for 61 yards. Pizzotti threw a 20-yard touchdown strike to Mike Cook with less than five minutes to play. Princeton used three quarterbacks. Bill Foran went 3-for-8 before leaving in the second half with a concussion. Greg Mroz and Brian Anderson each threw an interception, both to Crimson cornerback Steven Williams. Mazza had 71 yards receiving while Crimson tight end Jason Miller had 84 yards on three catches. Princeton holds a 52-41-7 lead in the series.
